    • enableDataLogs

      public static void enableDataLogs(String logPath)
      Enables DataLog recording of NT output.

      The wpilog is created at the logPath point. If the logPath ends with a forward slash, it is seen as a directory. Otherwise, it is seen as a file.

      Parameters:
      logPath - The path to store the logfile at.

    • disableDataLogs

      public static void disableDataLogs()
      Closes the existing DataLog file and resets it to null.

    • pubsubTypeMismatch

      public static void pubsubTypeMismatch(String key, String type, boolean isPub)
      Reports when a publisher or subscriber have inconsistent types with what is being logged or read.
      Parameters:
      key - The key being logged to or read.
      type - The class being logged.
      isPub - Whether or not the issue occurred with a publisher.

    • noSub

      public static void noSub(String key)
      Reports when a key does not have a subscriber to read from.
      Parameters:
      key - The key being read.

    • structTypeMismatch

      public static void structTypeMismatch(String key, String desiredType, String realType)
      Reports when the internal type of logged or read StructSerializable objects do not match what type is being requested.
      Parameters:
      key - The key being read.
      desiredType - The class the logger is attempting to read.
      realType - The class of the variable in NetworkTables.

    • log

      public static void log(String key, boolean[] value, String... aliases)
      Logs a boolean array to NetworkTables.

      It also creates any of the aliases passed into the array.

      Parameters:
      key - The key to log the value under. This can be a NetworkTables path or an alias.
      value - The boolean array to log.
      aliases - Any aliases to add to the ntPath.

    • addAliases

      public static void addAliases(String ntPath, String... aliases)
      Adds aliases to a key. Aliases are accepted as alternatives for the key in the TurboLogger.log or TurboLogger.get methods. They can also increase readability in the code.

      Aliases have their own entry in the lastRead table. This means that when you get an alias, it does not mark the main key or any other aliases for that key as read.

      Parameters:
      ntPath - The path to create an alias for.
      aliases - The aliases to add.

    • hasChanged

      public static boolean hasChanged(String key)
      Gets whether or not the logged value has changed since the last time the key was read from.
      Parameters:
      key - The key to check the status of. This can be the path in NetworkTables or an alias.
      Returns:
      Whether or not the logged value has changed.

    • remove

      public static void remove(String key)
      Removes a key from the logger.

      If the key is a NT path, then it removes its aliases. If the key is an alias itself, it removes the alias.

      Parameters:
      key - The key to remove.
